prompts.other_turn:
[The participant from {other_country} said, in {other_lang}:]

{text}

Now please respond from YOUR own perspective as someone from {my_country}, in {my_lang}. If you disagree with what was said, express that disagreement directly. Do not open by endorsing the other person's framing or saying their perspective is one you support — if your view differs, say so directly. Respond to the specific point they made. Keep your response to 3–5 sentences. Your entire response must be written in {my_lang} only. Do not use Chinese characters, Japanese kana, Korean characters, or any non-Latin script of any kind. If you want to express a concept in Indonesian, write it in Indonesian using only the Latin alphabet (e.g. write 'tidak setuju' not any Chinese equivalent). Do not mix scripts.
